 p.





Montreux, Palace Hotel

11-V-71

I was acutely aware, dear Andrew, upon re-reading the Sologub1 poems you kindly sent me how much I always admired parts of that Curate's Egg. A number of lines in the Palach are indeed first-rate—little musical storms blowing through this or that strophe; but there are also unacceptable neuklyuzhesti in many lines, and a quite hideous error of pronunciation in line 29: "scaffold" is pomóst, not the impossibly provincial—or simply wrong—pómost. It